3. triclinia. Generally explained to mean luxurious seats round the interior of the bath-rooms, but it may probably mean chambers opening out of the bath-roonis, such as the οἰκήματα εἰς τρυφὴν (al. τροφήν) παρεσκευασμένα, mentioned in Luciam Hippias c. 5. Cot-ta’s baths, it must be remembered, were excessively luxurious.
